    public abstract class ModuleWindow
extends InternalWindow
    A class responsible for creating and displaying a window that enables a user to input data for one of the RNAstructure modules.

      • makeStartButton

        protected final void makeStartButton(int x,
                                     int y)
        Create the "START" button.

        Note that this method simply makes the button, adds the action listener, applies standard padding, then places the button at the specified (X,Y) layout coordinate.

        If more customization of the button itself or its positioning is needed, it should be done in subclasses.
        Parameters:
        x - The X index at which to place the button in the layout.
        y - The Y index at which to place the button in the layout.

      • moduleInitialized

        protected final boolean moduleInitialized(java.lang.String result)
        Check to see if the module was initialized correctly.

        Check what the result string retrieved from the module was, and return true only if it's the empty string. Otherwise, show the result string as an error and return false.
        Parameters:
        result - The result of the data structure construction.
        Returns:
        True if the data structure was initialized correctly, false if not.
